/*
Container With Most Water - Easy Explanation

We use two pointers:
left starts at the beginning
right starts at the end

At each step:
1. Calculate width = right - left
2. Find smaller height using Math.min()
3. Area = width * smaller height
4. Update max area
5. Move the smaller height pointer

Reason:
The smaller wall limits the water level.
So moving the smaller pointer may help find a taller wall.

Time Complexity: O(n)
Space Complexity: O(1)

Memory Trick:
calculate area -> update max -> move smaller pointer
*/

width=index num only(right - left);
h=Math.min(heigth[left],height[right];
area=width*h;
